12. Risk Analysis
12.1 Founder Risks
Risk	Probability	Impact	Mitigation
Single founder	High	High	Build advisory board early
Technical debt	Medium	High	TDD from day one, 95% test coverage
Burnout	High	High	Strict work hours, self-care schedule
12.2 Market Risks
Low adoption: Freemium model, focus on underserved niches

Strong competition: Differentiation through specialization

Regulatory changes: Compliance-first architecture

12.3 Financial Risks
Cash flow issues: Conservative spending, 6-month runway target

Pricing pressure: Value-based pricing, not feature-based

Payment fraud: AI fraud detection from launch

13. Exit Strategy
13.1 Potential Outcomes
Acquisition (5-7 years): $150-300M by Calendly, Zoom, or education tech company

IPO (8-10 years): $1B+ valuation with $100M+ revenue

Sustainable Business: Profitable $50M/year business with 30% margins

Founder Buyout: Management team acquires business in 7-10 years

13.2 Founder Goals
Primary: Build sustainable, impactful business

Secondary: $50M+ exit in 7-10 years

Minimum Viable: $5M in 5 years (acquisition by competitor)

